               <head>A two-volume <title>Sharḥ-i Dīvān-i Ḥāfiẓ</title> (Commentary on the Divan of Ḥāfiẓ).</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>
                     The <title>Sharḥ-i Dīvān-i Ḥāfiẓ</title> (Ṣerḥ-i Dīvān-ı Ḥāfıẓ, Commentary on the Divan of Ḥāfiẓ), in two volumes together with Rylands <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7264"><idno>Persian MS 33b</idno></ref>. 
                     Aḥmad Sūdī Būsnavī completed this Ottoman Turkish commentary on the Persian Dīvān of Ḥāfiẓ (d. ca. 1390) at the request of his patron, the <hi rend="italic" xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc">Seyh̬ül-Ḥarem-i Yes̱rib</hi> (Shaykh al-Ḥaram-i Yathrib [Medina]),ʿUmar
                     Apparently originally completed as a single large tome, a former owner split the volume into two, hence this initial volume presents commentaries upon ghazals alphabetically arranged by the rhymed <hi>radīf</hi>, the final word in each line, with the letters alif to dāl, with those rhymed in dāl to yā ifound in the second volume. 
                  </summary>

                  <msItem>
                     <author role="com" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/32802306" key="person_32802306" change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" >Aḥmad Sūdī Būsnavī, d. ca. 1596</persName>
                     </author>
                     <author key="person_56731778" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/56731778/" role="ant" change="#role-assignment #ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Ḥāfiẓ, 14th cent.</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">‏حافظ شيرازى</persName></author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7020">Sharḥ-i Dīvān-i Ḥāfiẓ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7020">Ṣerḥ-i Dīvān-ı Ḥāfıẓ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_7020">شرح ديوان حافظ</title>
                     <note>In his introduction on folio <locus from="Vol_1_6b" to="Vol_1_6b">6b, line 5</locus>, the author stataes that the Seyh̬ül-Ḥarem-i Yes̱rib [Shaykh of Medina],ʿUmar
                        Efendī commissioned the work. Since the catchword
                        at the end of <locus from="Vol_1_481b" to="Vol_1_481b">VoL. 1 folio 481b</locus>, matches the first word on <locus from="Vol_2_8a" to="Vol_2_8a">Vol. II folio 8a</locus> it proves that a prior owner split a much larger volume into two and had them rebound as a set. Both volumes contain
                        preceding indexes; however,  <locus from="Vol_1_482a" to="Vol_1_482a">Vol. 1 folio 482a</locus> bears a colophon added
                        when divided into two volumes, whereas <locus from="Vol_2_509a" to="Vol_2_509b">Vol. 2 folio 509b</locus> contains the original colophon for the entire work.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ota">Persian and Ottoman Turkish</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
